This paper deals with the construction of distance oracles for graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses techniques from numerical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to numerical algorithms (cs.NA).
